entry.title: [Grid] Introduce caching of MinMaxSizes for subgrids
entry.content:
To complete the grid sizing algorithm for multiple levels of subgrids,

we need to compute the `MinMaxSizes` of standalone axes of subgrids to

get their contribution size or calculate its initial fragment geometry.



Previously, we computed these sizes on-demand each time. This change

introduces caching of the `MinMaxSizes` to be reused within the same

step of the sizing algorithm in `CompleteTrackSizingAlgorithm`.



Significant perf deltas:

- nested-subgrid

avg 57.945 runs/s -> 181.646 runs/s (213.5% better)



Bug: 1505606

entry.title: Allowing VA-API on Linux Ozone/Wayland
entry.content:
VaapiWrapper has been updated to remove the usage of libva-x11 and the

legacy VaapiVideoDecodeAccelerator, in favor of libva-drm only. This

means now Linux Ozone/Wayland can share the same code path as Linux

Ozone/X11. See CL:4938496.



This CL removes the remaining libva-x11 codes from Ozone and

VaapiWrapper, and allows VA-API by default on Linux Ozone/Wayland.



Insofar as Linux + VA-API is not a supported platform (IOW it's a best

effort) and this will allow developers and users to try and make it work

on their machines. [1]



[1]

https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/main/docs/gpu/vaapi.md#vaapi-on-linux



Test On Linux X11:

-enable-features=VaapiVideoDecodeLinuxGL \

--use-gl=angle --use-angle=gl \

--ozone-platform=x11



Test On Linux Wayland:

-enable-features=VaapiVideoDecodeLinuxGL \

--use-gl=angle --use-angle=gl \

--ozone-platform=wayland

entry.title: [shared storage] Use a separate backing thread for each worklet
entry.content:
We originally intended to use one dedicated thread per worklet,

but inadvertently implemented our design using a shared backing

thread.



While both approaches should function correctly, we suspect that

this shared-thread implementation may be related to a recent crash

(see the bug). Therefore, we're proactively switching to the

originally intended design of one dedicated thread per worklet.

We follow the pattern for shared worker and dedicated worker, that

configures to use AtomicsWaitMode::kAllow.



We will continue to monitor the situation, and we can revert this

change if necessary.

entry.title: Remove `used_ssl_config` from HttpStreamFactory's callbacks.
entry.content:
Despite the name, it's not actually the SSLConfig that was used - in

particular, on cert errors, its `allowed_bad_certs` field contains

the certificate and error that was encountered, instead of being the

value that was used when establishing the connection. The rest of

the fields are what was used, but those fields are never actually

used - they're overwritten if the `used_proxy_config` is used to try

to reconnect to the server, ignoring the previous SSL error.



Moreover, the HttpStreamFactory callbacks already have information

about any SSL certificate error that was just received, in the passed

in SSLInfo. So this CL makes HttpNetworkTransaction accumulate them

itself in its OnCertificateError() callback, instead of having the

HttpStreamFactory layer pass them back in a roundabout manner.



When restarting a request, the accumulated information is coped to

a new SSLConfig's `allowed_bad_certs` that's passed to the

HttpStreamFactory layer, as before, just without all the other fields

needlessly set.



In a followup CL, we'll switch to passing allowed bad cert information

directly to the HttpStreamFactory layer.



Bug: 1498285

entry.title: Support setting a proxy chain and header name in TestProxyDelegate
entry.content:
This CL updates TestProxyDelegate to allow setting a proxy chain that

should be used for a given URL and also makes adding a header to the

CONNECT requests optional (and the user specifies what the name should

be). This allows us to consolidate test ProxyDelegates.



As part of this refactoring, I noticed that the

ReconsiderProxyAfterFirstNestedProxyErrorHttps unit test wasn't

working as expected - in the kTunnelRead error case, the read error

seemed to be consumed first and the write never consumed. This is

different than how it works for ReconsiderProxyAfterErrorHttpsProxy

and ReconsiderProxyAfterSecondNestedProxyErrorHttps, which are

conceptually very similar. I switched this test to use

SequencedSocketData instead of StaticSocketDataProvider and this

seems to have addressed the issue.



Bug: 1491092
